\chapter{Command-Line Interface}
\label{cli}

The [[learnlog]] command lets teachers and teaching assistants
review the development logs that students produce.
It provides nine subcommands: [[list]] gives a compact overview
of the recorded commits, [[export]] creates a portable bundle of
the log (or a ProgSnap2 dataset for CS education analysis),
[[set-remote]], [[push]], [[clone]], and [[pull]] manage
synchronisation with a remote Git repository, [[git]] forwards
Git commands to the log repository, [[tag]] manages named
markers in the log (such as [[lab1]] or [[lab2]]), and [[play]]
gives an interactive viewer for browsing the commit history.

We use Typer for the CLI framework because it gives us type-checked
arguments with minimal boilerplate, and the modern
[[Annotated]] style makes the parameter declarations self-documenting.


