\section{Resolving the source}

The [[play]] command accepts an optional source that can be a
directory (containing [[.learnlog/]]) or a bundle file.
We need a single function that resolves any of these into a
[[LearnlogRepo]] ready for querying.

For bundle files, we clone them into a temporary directory.
The caller is responsible for cleanup---we return both the repo
and the temporary directory (or [[None]] if no temp dir was created).

We detect bundles by checking whether [[git bundle verify]]
succeeds on the file, rather than relying on file extensions.
This is more robust: a user might name their bundle
[[student-log.bin]] instead of [[student.bundle]].

<<helper functions>>=
def resolve_source(source=None):
    """Resolve a source into a ``(LearnlogRepo, tmpdir)`` pair.

    ``source`` can be ``None`` (search current directory),
    a directory path, or a bundle file.  When a bundle is used,
    ``tmpdir`` is the temporary directory that should be cleaned
    up by the caller; otherwise it is ``None``.
    """
    if source is None:
        workdir = find_learnlog_dir()
        if workdir is None:
            raise SystemExit(
                "No .learnlog/ directory found. "
                "Run this from a learnlog-tracked project."
            )
        return LearnlogRepo(workdir), None

    path = pathlib.Path(source).resolve()

    if path.is_dir():
        if not (path / ".learnlog").is_dir():
            raise SystemExit(
                f"No .learnlog/ directory in {path}"
            )
        return LearnlogRepo(path), None

    <<resolve bundle file>>
@

To unbundle, we create a temporary directory and use
[[git clone]] with the bundle as the remote.
We point [[GIT_DIR]] at the cloned repo's [[.git/]] so that
[[LearnlogRepo.git()]] can query it.
However, [[LearnlogRepo]] expects the git directory to be named
[[.learnlog/]], so we rename it after cloning.

<<resolve bundle file>>=
if not path.is_file():
    raise SystemExit(f"Not a file or directory: {path}")

verify = subprocess.run(
    ["git", "bundle", "verify", str(path)],
    capture_output=True, text=True,
)
if verify.returncode != 0:
    raise SystemExit(
        f"Not a valid bundle file: {path}"
    )

tmpdir = tempfile.mkdtemp(prefix="learnlog-play-")
tmppath = pathlib.Path(tmpdir)

subprocess.run(
    ["git", "clone", str(path), str(tmppath / "repo")],
    capture_output=True, text=True, check=True,
)

cloned = tmppath / "repo"
(cloned / ".git").rename(cloned / ".learnlog")

return LearnlogRepo(cloned), tmpdir
@

