\subsection{The [[export]] command}

The [[export]] command resolves the learnlog directory using
[[resolve_workdir]] and delegates to [[do_export]] or
[[do_export_progsnap2]] depending on the [[--progsnap2]] flag.
It uses [[-C]] / [[--dir]] rather than [[resolve_source]] because
export does not need bundle support---we are \emph{creating}
bundles, not reading them.

When [[--progsnap2]] is set, the default output changes from
[[learnlog.bundle]] to [[learnlog.progsnap2]].
We detect this by checking whether the user explicitly passed
[[-o]]---if the output still equals the bundle default, we
substitute the ProgSnap2 default.

<<typer commands>>=
@app.command()
def export(
    output: Annotated[
        pathlib.Path,
        typer.Option(
            "--output", "-o",
            help="Output file path.",
        ),
    ] = pathlib.Path(DEFAULT_BUNDLE_NAME),
    directory: Annotated[
        Optional[pathlib.Path],
        typer.Option(
            "--dir", "-C",
            help="Directory containing .learnlog/.",
        ),
    ] = None,
    progsnap2: Annotated[
        bool,
        typer.Option(
            "--progsnap2",
            help=(
                "Export as ProgSnap2 zip instead of "
                "a Git bundle."
            ),
        ),
    ] = False,
):
    """Export the learnlog repository."""
    workdir = resolve_workdir(directory)
    repo = LearnlogRepo(workdir)

    if progsnap2:
        if output == pathlib.Path(DEFAULT_BUNDLE_NAME):
            output = pathlib.Path(
                DEFAULT_PROGSNAP2_NAME
            )
        do_export_progsnap2(repo, output.resolve())
    else:
        do_export(repo, output.resolve())

    typer.echo(f"Exported to {output}")
@

