\subsection{The [[tag]] command}
\label{sec:tag}

While [[learnlog git tag lab1]] already works via the
[[git]] passthrough, typing [[learnlog tag lab1]] is more
discoverable---students see it in [[learnlog --help]]
alongside [[play]] and [[export]], which reinforces that
tagging is a first-class operation rather than a Git
implementation detail.

The implementation mirrors the [[git]] passthrough
(\cref{sec:git}): we find the [[.learnlog/]] directory,
set the Git environment, and forward all arguments to
