\subsection{The [[play]] command}
\label{sec:play}

The most common use of [[play]] is jumping to a tagged
session: [[learnlog play lab1]] starts playback from the
commit tagged [[lab1]].
Therefore the optional positional argument is a Git ref
(tag name, branch, or commit hash), not the source
directory.
The source---a directory containing [[.learnlog/]] or a
bundle file---is specified with [[--from]] / [[-f]] when
needed; it defaults to the current directory.

The [[-b]] / [[--batch]] flag selects batch mode
(\cref{sec:play-batch}), which prints all commits to standard
output instead of launching the curses viewer.
When the flag is not given explicitly, we auto-detect: if
standard output is not a terminal (for example when piped to
[[less]]), batch mode activates automatically.
This means [[learnlog play | less]] just works without the user
having to remember the flag.

By default, learnlog's own runs are filtered from the output
(\cref{sec:filter-learnlog}).
The [[--all]] / [[-a]] flag disables this filter, showing every
run block including those from [[learnlog play]] and
[[learnlog export]] invocations.

<<typer commands>>=
@app.command()
def play(
    start: Annotated[
        Optional[str],
        typer.Argument(
            help=(
                "Tag, commit hash, or branch to start "
                "playback from."
            ),
        ),
    ] = None,
    source: Annotated[
        Optional[str],
        typer.Option(
            "--from", "-f",
            help=(
                "Source: directory with .learnlog/ "
                "or a .bundle file. "
                "Defaults to current directory."
            ),
        ),
    ] = None,
    batch: Annotated[
        Optional[bool],
        typer.Option(
            "--batch", "-b",
            help=(
                "Print all commits to stdout instead of "
                "the interactive viewer.  Auto-enabled "
                "when stdout is not a terminal."
            ),
        ),
    ] = None,
    show_all: Annotated[
        bool,
        typer.Option(
            "--all", "-a",
            help=(
                "Include learnlog's own runs in the "
                "output."
            ),
        ),
    ] = False,
):
    """Interactively play back the development log."""
    import shutil

    repo, tmpdir = resolve_source(source)
    try:
        commits = get_commits(repo)
        if not commits:
            raise SystemExit("No commits found.")

        start_index = 0
        if start:
            <<find starting commit index>>

        <<choose playback mode>>
    finally:
        if tmpdir is not None:
            shutil.rmtree(tmpdir, ignore_errors=True)
