We resolve the starting ref through [[git rev-parse]], which
handles tag names, branch names, and abbreviated hashes
uniformly.
If [[rev-parse]] fails (for example, a typo), we fall back
to prefix matching on the commit list---this covers the
case where a short hash is ambiguous in Git but unique among
the commits we have.

<<find starting commit index>>=
resolved = repo.git("rev-parse", start)
if resolved.returncode == 0:
    full_hash = resolved.stdout.strip()
    for i, c in enumerate(commits):
        if c["hash"] == full_hash:
            start_index = i
            break
    else:
        raise SystemExit(
            f"Ref {start} resolves to "
            f"{full_hash[:8]} which is not "
            f"in the commit list."
        )
else:
    for i, c in enumerate(commits):
        if c["hash"].startswith(start):
            start_index = i
            break
    else:
        raise SystemExit(
            f"Commit {start} not found."
        )
@

